<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="469" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">Description.</emphasis>
Body medium sized, 6.2~8.7 mm in length (including tegmen). Head apex in dorsal view arcuately produced, median longitudinal carina lamellate (
<figureCitation box="[827,1000,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[888,935,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[952,1000,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
); submarginal carina concentrated on head, and furcated in front of ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[563,721,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[620,664,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[677,721,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
); area between median carina and submarginal carina distinctly concave, without longitudinal striae (
<figureCitation box="[582,754,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[643,691,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[706,754,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vertex between eyes shorter than wide, and shorter than pronotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[451,625,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[512,560,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[577,625,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ocelli small, located laterad of submarginal carina, about half way between eye and apex (
<figureCitation box="[413,571,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[470,513,332,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[527,571,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum broad, wider than head, length shorter than half width (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[1386,1431,332,356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[151,196,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum triangular, shorter than pronotum, with transverse depression distinct, usually black or with black markings (
<figureCitation box="[270,426,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[326,370,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[382,426,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Face including eyes, longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[886,1042,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[943,987,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="2.4">2, 4</number>
, 
<number box="[999,1042,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="6.8">6, 8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeus broad and swollen at base, with median longitudinal carina strongly elevated, laterally obliquely striate, usually light yellow with three black markings: one dorsomedially and one on each side of longitudinal carina; lora nearly reaching apex of clypellus (
<figureCitation box="[269,437,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[329,375,512,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="2.4">2, 4</number>
, 
<number box="[390,437,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="6.8">6, 8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing veins slightly prominent, with R 
<number box="[951,957,526,540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.0">1</number>
a; four apical cells; appendix very narrow (
<figureCitation box="[159,317,550,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[283,1300,405,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[282,1304,405,1905]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Body dorsal view and ventral view (♂). 1 – 2, Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov.. 3 – 4, Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov .. 5 – 6, Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov.. 7 – 8, Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230474/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[216,260,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
, 
<number box="[272,317,550,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="5.7">5, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Front tibia with dorsal macrosetae 
<number box="[729,741,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[762,774,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.0">1</number>
, AV well developed. 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1072,550,575]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg apical femoral setal formula 
<number box="[151,166,587,611]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="2.0">2</number>
+0. Middle trochanter with scattered fine setae ventrally; femur broader and slightly shorter than front femur, setal rows indistinct; tibia with dorsal setae 
<number box="[582,594,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[615,627,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.0">1</number>
, ventral rows with few widely spaced setae; PD setae subequal in length (terminology for leg chaetotaxy following 
<bibRefCitation author="Dietrich" box="[629,816,658,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" refString="Dietrich, C. H. (2004) Phylogeny of the leafhopper subfamily Evacanthinae with a review of Neotropical species and notes on related groups (Hemiptera: Membracoidea: Cicadellidae). Systematic Entomology, 29, 455 - 487. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 0307 - 6970.2004.00250. x" type="journal article" year="2004">
Dietrich (
<number box="[736,797,659,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="2004.0">2004</number>
))
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Male pygofer without ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[641,729,694,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1252,1274]" captionTargetBox="[182,1428,305,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[174,1459,303,1219]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov. 9. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 10. Head and thorax, lateral view; 11. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 13. Connective and style, ventral view; 14. Male pygofer, lateral view; 15. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[699,729,695,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="14.19">14</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[742,772,695,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,988,1010]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,199,943]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,964]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 20. Shortcrowna flavocapitata comb. nov. 16. Aedeagus, style and connective, lateral view; 17. Aedeagus, style and connective, ventral view; 18. Style and connective, ventral view; 19. Male pygofer, lateral view; 20. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230476/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">19</figureCitation>
, 
<number box="[786,861,695,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="24.29">
<figureCitation box="[786,817,695,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 25" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1970,1992]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,1308,1955]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[156,1441,1303,1957]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 25. Shortcrowna nigrimargina comb. nov. 21. Aedeagus, style and connective, lateral view; 22. Aedeagus, style and connective, ventral view; 23. Style and connective, ventral view; 24. Male pygofer, lateral view; 25. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230477/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[829,861,695,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 30" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,1067,1758]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[156,1441,1062,1762]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 30. Shortcrowna leishanensis sp. nov. 26. Aedeagus, style and connective, lateral view; 27. Aedeagus, style and connective, ventral view; 28. Aedeagus, style and connective, dorsal view; 29. Male pygofer, lateral view; 30. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230478/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">29</figureCitation>
</number>
). Subgenital plate elongate, macrosetae irregularly distributed, two rows of setae along inner submargin (
<figureCitation box="[763,894,730,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1252,1274]" captionTargetBox="[182,1428,305,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[174,1459,303,1219]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Shortcrowna biguttata comb. nov. 9. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 10. Head and thorax, lateral view; 11. Aedeagus, connective and style, lateral view; 12. Aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view; 13. Connective and style, ventral view; 14. Male pygofer, lateral view; 15. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
Figs 
<number box="[821,894,730,755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="14.15">14, 15</number>
