<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="469" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1126,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus is very similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[819,1004,1126,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bundera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[819,916,1127,1151]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="469">Bundera</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
externally, but it can be distinguished from the latter by: 
<number box="[367,379,1163,1187]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="1.0">1</number>
) body relatively large; 
<number box="[650,665,1163,1187]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="2.0">2</number>
) vertex between eyes about as long as wide or slightly shorter than wide; 
<number box="[220,234,1199,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="469" value="3.0">3</number>
) aedeagal shaft tubular, somewhat recurved dorsally, with paired membranous lobes near middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
